721157f-a.title: Manhattan: MacDougal Street - Prince Street
721157f-a.text:
Macdogal Street, south from and including the junction of Charlton
Street, on the west side, and Prince Street, on the east. The
drug store at the right is 2 Charlton Street, and will be de-
Riolished the year after this view, together with the rest of the
west side of Macdougal Street from Charlton to Van Dam Streets.
No. 34 Macdougal Strcet, at the S.E. corner of Prince Street, will
become 204 Sixth Avenue, No. 32 is the Second Assebly District
Republican Club, and No. 28 (future 198 Sixth Avenue), next to
the five-story police station, which is flying the flag, is, or
used to be, the Richmond Hill settlement house, named efter the
Richmond Hill mansion which stood in what is now the middle of
Charlton Street (q.v.) between Macdougal and Varick Streets.
Charlton Street received its present name in 1807, and has so far
escaped being hade an extension of Frince Street, the way Brannon
Street was swallowed by Spring Street, and (later), Hammersley
by Houston (2.v.).
1926.
